Fifty per cent of Americans are calling for the legalisation of marijuana - a record high - according to a new Gallup poll.

Gaining steady support, the number is up from 46 per cent last year and has climbed from 12 per cent since 1969, when the research firm first asked about legalising marijuana.

The findings come months after the Obama administration toughened its stand on medical marijuana in the 16 states where pot is legal for people with doctors' 
recommendations.

