Liberals are twice as likely as conservatives to favour legalizing marijuana, with relative 69 and 34 per cent approval ratings.

And Democrats and independents, both 
at 57 per cent, are more likely to be in favour than are Republicans, 35
per cent of which support the legalisation of marijuana.

